JOHANNESBURG - Berning Ntlemeza's appeal to be reinstated as the head of the Hawks has been dismissed from the Supreme Court of Appeal on Friday.READ: Ntlemeza argues his reputation is at stakeNtlemeza's legal team asked the presiding judges to overturn the April ruling that he could not continue as Hawks boss.The North Gauteng High Court had previously struck his case from the roll saying his appointment was irrational and unlawful.eNCA